## Core Agents (always present)

### Nexus — Orchestrator

**Owns:** Session management, task routing, planning gates, sub-agent review
**Must NOT touch:** Any source code (enforced by `disallowedTools: Write, Edit, NotebookEdit`)
**Routing triggers:** Every task passes through Nexus; Nexus routes by domain, never implements

### Scout — Investigator

**Owns:** Read-only exploration; semantic search; pre-implementation discovery; reflection step
**Must NOT touch:** Anything (enforced by `disallowedTools: Edit, Write, NotebookEdit`)
**Routing triggers:** Investigation / unknown territory / pre-implementation scouting / multi-domain discovery
**Model:** claude-haiku-4-5 (high-volume read-only; cheap discovery)

### Lens — Validator

**Owns:** Acceptance verification; deterministic + semantic review; revision reports
**Must NOT touch:** Anything (enforced by `disallowedTools: Edit, Write, NotebookEdit`)
**Routing triggers:** After EVERY implementer completion (Rule 17 — Lens validates before NEXUS:DONE accepted)
**Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6

### Quill — Test Author

**Owns:** Test stubs (before implementation); test verification (after implementation)
**Must NOT touch:** Production source files; `.memory/`
**Routing triggers:** Before any implementer begins (stubs); after implementer completes (pass verification)
**Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6

