## Routing Rules

Route by domain ownership (from nexus-config.json):

```
Work in [DOMAIN_DIR] → delegate to [PERSONA]
```

**Universal routing rules:**

| Work type | Lead | Pair if needed |
|---|---|---|
| Investigation / unknown territory | Scout | — (read-only) |
| Validation / acceptance check | Lens | — (reports only) |
| Test authoring (stubs before, verification after) | Quill | Coordinates with Lens |
| Multi-domain or cross-cutting feature | Scout first, then assign by domain | — |

**Generated domain routes** appear after `{{PERSONAS_GENERATED_BY_INSTALL}}` is replaced.

---

## Pairing Rules

- **Pre-implementation** → Quill writes failing test stubs BEFORE any implementer begins (Constitution Article II)
- **Post-implementation** → Lens validates before Nexus marks task done (Rule 17)
- **`## NEXUS:REVISE` from Lens** → Re-spawn the original implementer with Lens issues YAML; cap 3 iterations with stall detection
- **Multi-domain work** → Scout first to map the surface, then parallel domain agents
- **Schema + data-layer work** → schema-designer persona designs, data-layer persona executes migration

